Spaghetti Plot

spgtplot.Rd

Generate a flexible facet spaghetti plot for endpoint analysis

spgtplot(data, group_by, x, y, subj = "USUBJID", title = "",
  xlab = "Visit Day", ylab = "AVAL", symb = NULL, caption = "")

Arguments

data

a dataframe containing the input data to plot
group_by

a column name containing factors to split the plot by
x

column name for x-axis parameter
y

column name for y-axis parameter
subj

column name for unique subject identifier, default is "USUBJID"
title

custom plot title, passed as a string
xlab

custom x-axis plot label, passed as string
ylab

custom y-axis plot label, passed as a string
symb

optional parameter to shape markers by a factor type column
caption

optional string to include as a caption on bottom of plot

Value

produces a spaghetti plot with study endpoint measurements over time that can be facet by a factor-class column variable

Examples

spgtplot(data = AZA, group_by = "CHRTGRP", x = "ADY", y = "AVAL", symb = "EPOCH")
